"title": "4615: bull",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4615",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Bulls were particularly prized as sacrifices on account of their considerable value. The sacrifice of a bull was especially associated with the sin offering.</p>\n<h2>Bulls offered as sacrifices</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:36\">EXO 29:36</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:12-2Sam6:13\">2SA 6:12–6:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:13\">ACT 14:13</a></strong> <em>Also used in pagan sacrifices.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:1-Num23:4\">NUM 23:1–23:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:7-Job42:8\">JOB 42:7–42:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:15\">PSA 66:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:13\">HEB 9:13</a></p>\n<h3>Instructions for the offering of a bull</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13-Lev4:21\">LEV 4:13–4:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:3-Lev1:9\">LEV 1:3–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Bulls sacrificed on significant occasions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:16-Num28:20\">NUM 28:16–28:20</a></strong> <em>The Passover.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4-Exod24:5\">EXO 24:4–24:5</a> <em>the covenant confirmed</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:10-Exod29:14\">EXO 29:10–29:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:2\">LEV 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:11-Lev16:14\">LEV 16:11–16:14</a> <em>the Day of Atonement</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:5-Num8:12\">NUM 8:5–8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12-Num29:13\">NUM 29:12–29:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:24\">1SA 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:25-1Chr15:26\">1CH 15:25–15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:21-1Chr29:22\">1CH 29:21–29:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:20-2Chr29:24\">2CH 29:20–29:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:9-Ezra6:10\">EZR 6:9–6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:35\">EZR 8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:19-Ezek43:27\">EZK 43:19–43:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:18-Ezek45:24\">EZK 45:18–45:24</a></p>\n<h3>Godly sacrifices in contrast to pagan ones</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:22-1Kgs18:24\">1KI 18:22–18:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:25-Judg6:28\">JDG 6:25–6:28</a></p>\n<h2>Even the sacrifice of bulls invalid without the spiritual conditions being fulfilled</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:30-Ps69:31\">PSA 69:30–69:31</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11\">ISA 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:9\">PSA 50:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:13\">PSA 50:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:3\">ISA 66:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:11\">HOS 12:11</a></p>\n<h2>Provisional nature of the OT sin offering of a bull</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:4\">HEB 10:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The bull as a symbol of strength</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:17\">DEU 33:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:12\">PSA 22:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:30\">PSA 68:30</a></p>\n<h2>Laws concerning bulls</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:28-Exod21:36\">EXO 21:28–21:36</a></p>\n<h2>Bulls in the design of the temple</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:25-1Kgs7:29\">1KI 7:25–7:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:3-2Chr4:4\">2CH 4:3–4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:17\">2KI 16:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:20\">JER 52:20</a></p>\n<h2>Bulls in the setting of judgment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:6-Isa34:7\">ISA 34:6–34:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:27\">JER 50:27</a></p>\n<h2>Bulls and idolatry</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:20\">PSA 106:20</a></p>",
